{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes you may want to execute some logic just after the user clicks on a column header.\par
\par
To do this, just create an Event Handler for the Column Click event. The event passes one variable, which is the name of the column that was clicked on.\par
\par
In this example, a message is given when you click on the column header, giving the name of the column. \par
